			<abstract>
				<p>Testimony of Wolf Fajnsztadt, who was in Ostrowiec Świętokrzyski, regarding the resistance movement in the ghetto and attempts to obtain weapons. On July 26, 1944, a group of 29 young Jewish inmates escaped into the woods and undertook guerilla warfare in the vicinity of
					Krzeminki, Czarna Glinka, and Ruda Kościelna.</p>
			</abstract>
