					<!--<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_fajnsztadt_wolf">Wolf Fajnsztadt</persName> Testimony (doc.
        301/945)</p>
      <p>Typescript, 2 pages, 210 x 295 mm, Polish language</p>-->
					<pb facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010945_01.jpg" n="1"/>
					<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_fajnsztadt_wolf">Wolf Fajnsztadt</persName><note type="gloss">In the later part of the text he is called Fajnstok.</note> born on <date when="1919-11-15">November 15, 1919</date>, in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html"
							>Lublin</placeName>. Father <persName ref="#ehri_et_fajnsztadt_mojzesz">Mojżesz</persName>, mother <persName ref="#ehri_et_mendelewicz_chana">Chana Mendelewicz</persName>. Before the war he lived in <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/762863/ostrowiec-swietokrzyski.htmll">Ostrowiec [Świętokrzyski]</placeName>. At present [residing in] <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3103719/bedzin.html">Będzin</placeName>, <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3103719/bedzin.html"
							>9 Potockiego Street</placeName>.</p>
					<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1215" type="subject">Partisan</term> fighting</p>
					<p>I was a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1215" type="subject">partisan</term> from <date when="1944-07-26">July 26, [1944]</date>, until <date when="1945-01-17">January 17, 1945</date>. Before my time as a <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1215" type="subject">partisan</term> I was in a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term> in <placeName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-1813" type="camp">Ostrowiec Świętokrzyski</placeName>.</p>
					<p>In <date when="1943-02">February 1943</date>, still in the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-15" type="ghetto">ghetto</placeName>, boys had organised an attack on the commandant of the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-566" type="subject">Jewish militia</term>, and we took away from him 40 <note type="gloss">Probably dollars.</note> in gold, the sum which we spent on arms. We exchanged that currency for 36 thousand zlotys, and
						bought 12 revolvers with this money. For the time being, we were in the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-15" type="ghetto">ghetto</placeName>. Seventeen of our boys went to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/767020/kunow.html"
							>Kunów</placeName> to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">hide</term> there on <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-183" type="subject">Aryan papers</term>, but they were <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">killed</term> by the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-312">AK</orgName> men. Those men threw a grenade into the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">bunker</term> where our friends were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">hiding</term>, and all of them were <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">killed</term> on that occasion. This delayed our action in the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-15" type="ghetto">ghetto</placeName> until <date when="1944-03"
							>March 1944</date>. At the beginning there were 47 of us, and only 30 members remained alive. The leaders of our fighting unit were two <persName ref="#ehri_et_stein">Stein</persName> brothers from <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/762863/ostrowiec-swietokrzyski.html">Ostrowiec.</placeName>. Both of them were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">killed</term> in <date when="1944-06">June 1944</date> during the talks with the
						boss of the workers’ party from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/762863/ostrowiec-swietokrzyski.html">Ostrowiec</placeName>. His name was <persName ref="#ehri_et_rybowski">Rybowski</persName>, alias <q><persName ref="#ehri_et_rybowski">Wujo</persName></q> [Uncle], and
						he was a <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_poles" type="subject">Pole</term>. They met to discuss the question of an <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">escape</term> attempt from the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term>. And then one Jew named <persName ref="#ehri_et_blumental">Blumental</persName>, a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-485" type="subject">capo</term> from
							<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-1813" type="camp">Ostrowiec</placeName>, informed on them to the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans" type="subject">Germans</term>, who immediately apprehended them, and the <persName
							ref="#ehri_et_stein">Stein</persName> brothers were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">executed</term> by a firing squad two days later. It took place in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508"
							type="subject">camp</term> square in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/762863/ostrowiec-swietokrzyski.html">Ostrowiec</placeName>.</p>
					<p>After that <persName ref="#ehri_et_kepinski_dawid">Dawid Kepiński</persName> from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3095321/konin.html">Konin</placeName> took over the command. Led by him, we cut through the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term> wires and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">escaped</term> to the forest on <date when="1944-07-25">July 25, 1944</date>. There were 29
						of us. We had 14 revolvers, 2 short machine guns, and 3 grenades. Thanks to <persName ref="#ehri_et_cukierman_antek">Antek Cukierman</persName> we received money from a <orgName ref="#ehri_et_jewish_fighting_organisation">Jewish fighting organisation</orgName> from <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Warsaw</placeName>. That money was brought by <persName ref="#ehri_et_beatus_frania">Frania Beatus</persName>, a Jewish <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">woman</term> from
							<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3095321/konin.html">Konin</placeName>. She brought 25,000 zlotys and one grenade. She came to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term> on <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-183" type="subject">Aryan papers</term>. As one group of the Jews from the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-1813" type="camp">Ostrowiec</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term> worked in the town on the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-373" type="subject">Aryan</term> side, she joined that group of workers when they were coming
						back to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term>, and in this way she also got into the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term> and established contact with us. On
						the following morning she returned with the same group to the town, but from there she went to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Warsaw</placeName>. But on the way some <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans" type="subject">Germans</term>
						recognised she was Jewish and she was <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">killed</term>.</p>
					<p>We stored the arms in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term> - in crates, feather quilts, and so on. When we entered the forest, in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/767292/krzemionki.html">Krzemionki</placeName>
						near <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/762863/ostrowiec-swietokrzyski.html">Ostrowiec</placeName>, we joined a <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_russians" type="subject">Russian</term> unit of nine. They had <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">escaped</term> from <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans" type="subject">German</term> captivity. They were well armed - they had eight machine guns. We contacted them through a <term
							ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_poles" type="subject">Pole</term> named <persName ref="#ehri_et_sternik">Sternik</persName> from the workers’ party from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/762863/ostrowiec-swietokrzyski.html">Ostrowiec</placeName> (he is at present a
						commandant of the militia in the Security Department in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/775737/bodzechow.html">Bodzechów</placeName><note type="gloss">W tekście: Bodzanowie.</note> near <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/762863/ostrowiec-swietokrzyski.html"
							>Ostrowiec</placeName>). We built three sheds because it was still <date when="1944">summer</date>, and in <date when="1944-09">September</date> we made up <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">underground bunkers</term>, the
						so-called <q><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">dug-outs</term></q>. There were four <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">bunkers</term> for thirty-eight people. There were also <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">girls</term>, about 20 years old, among us. They cooked for us.</p>
					<p>We <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">escaped</term> from the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term> because we were aware that it was going to be <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-551" type="subject">liquidated</term>. We were also planning to save our <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">families</term> but, unfortunately, it was too late. On <date
							when="1944-08-02">August 2, 1944</date>, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject">camp</term> was evacuated to <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0" type="camp">Auschwitz</placeName>, because the
						front was drawing nearer.</p>
					<p>We obtained <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">food</term> from well-off peasants and manors, and we paid for the products the pre-war prices. We went to get the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832"
							type="subject">food</term> at night, and we were armed. From time to time we met <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans" type="subject">Germans</term> at those peasants’ homes, and then the shooting ensued. On one such occasion four our boys were <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">killed</term> and two were wounded. But also two <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans" type="subject">Germans</term> were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745"
							type="subject">killed</term>, and we took off their uniforms and got hold of their arms, and went back to the forest. One day we met a <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans" type="subject">German</term> lorry which had a cargo of cigarettes and canned <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">food</term>. We <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">killed</term> two <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans" type="subject">Germans</term>, seized
						the cargo, and burnt the lorry, having first poured petrol on it. On <date when="1944-06-29">June 29, 1944</date>, we derailed a <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans" type="subject">German</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-940" type="subject">train</term> which was carrying ammunition and explosives to the front. On <date when="1944-10-04">October 4</date> we blew up the whole building in the village of <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/757836/sudol.html">Sudół Górny</placeName>,<note type="gloss">In the text: Sudogóra</note> in which a <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans" type="subject">German</term> Hauptmann <note type="gloss">Hauptmann (Ger.) – captain.</note> was
						staying. That <foreign xml:lang="de">Hauptmann</foreign> was <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">killed</term>, and we managed to run away. In <date when="1944-11">November</date> there was an ambush organised by the <term
							ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans" type="subject">Germans</term>, because we had been given away by one forester who told them where we were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hiding</term>. <pb
							facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3010945_02.jpg" n="2"/> The <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans" type="subject">Germans</term> came to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">bunker</term> and opened fire. Certainly, we fought back.
						Eight of our people were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">killed</term> at that time, including those two <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">girls</term> and one <term
							ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_russians" type="subject">Russian</term>. As there were sixty <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans" type="subject">Germans</term>, we had to withdraw and we <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject"
							>fled</term> to the forest in the village of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/773937/czarna-glina.html">Czarna Glinka</placeName><note type="gloss">In the text: Czarna Glina. </note> near <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/762863/ostrowiec-swietokrzyski.html"
							>Ostrowiec</placeName>. We built three new <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">bunkers</term> there. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">conditions</term> were harsh because we
						were persecuted by <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-312">AK</orgName> groups and the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans" type="subject">Germans</term> wherever we moved. Only armed individuals could go out to obtain <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">food</term>. We had run out of money by that time, so we took the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">food</term> from peasants without paying.
						Towards the end of <date when="1944-12">December</date> we were surrounded by a <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_hungarians">Hungarian</term> detachment which was allied with the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans" type="subject">Germans</term>. Severe fighting
						followed again. A lot of our people were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">killed</term>. Only six of us survived: five Jews and a <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_russians" type="subject">Russian</term>. We <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">escaped</term> to the forest in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/760126/ruda-koscielna.html">Ruda Kościelna</placeName> near <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/762863/ostrowiec-swietokrzyski.html">Ostrowiec</placeName>, where we hid in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">bunkers</term> for three weeks until the arrival of the <term
							ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_russians" type="subject">Russians</term>. We belonged to the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-313">Armia Ludowa</orgName>. We received newsletters and front news from the Main <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1215" type="subject">Partisan</term> Headquarters in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/762863/ostrowiec-swietokrzyski.html">Ostrowiec</placeName>. We were given those papers by the liaison officer <persName
							ref="#ehri_et_sternik">Sternik</persName>.</p>
					<p>The names of the members of that <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1215" type="subject">partisan</term> unit:</p>
					<p>1. <persName ref="#ehri_et_wajzer_mojzesz">Mojżesz Wajzer</persName> aged 28</p>
					<p>2. <persName ref="#ehri_et_szerman_borek">Berek Szerman</persName> 28</p>
					<p>3. <persName ref="#ehri_et_szerman_wolf">Wolf Szerman</persName> 52</p>
					<p>4. <persName ref="#ehri_et_waldman_matla">Matla Waldman</persName> 20</p>
					<p>5. <persName ref="#ehri_et_weinberg_szyfra">Szyfra Weinberg</persName> 20</p>
					<p>6. <persName ref="#ehri_et_fleischmann_majer">Majer Fleischmann</persName> 32</p>
					<p>7. <persName ref="#ehri_et_fleischmann_izrael">Izrael Fleischmann</persName> 24</p>
					<p>8. <persName ref="#ehri_et_fachler_tojwie">Tojwie Fachler</persName> 31</p>
					<p>9. <persName ref="#ehri_et_fachler_jakub">Jakub Fachler</persName> 22</p>
					<p>10. <persName ref="#ehri_et_fachler_szmul">Szmul Fachler</persName> 29</p>
					<p>11. <persName ref="#ehri_et_waserman_mendel">Mendel Waserman</persName> 21</p>
					<p>12. <persName ref="#ehri_et_rubinsztejn_uszer">Uszer Rubinsztejn</persName> 18</p>
					<p>13. <persName ref="#ehri_et_wajnberg_josef">Josef Wajnberg</persName> 22</p>
					<p>All of them come from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/762863/ostrowiec-swietokrzyski.html">Ostrowiec</placeName>.</p>
					<p>14. <persName ref="#ehri_et_slodki_izrael">Izrael Słodki</persName> 22</p>
					<p>15. <persName ref="#ehri_et_kempinski_szymon">Szymon Kempiński</persName> 28</p>
					<p>16. <persName ref="#ehri_et_kempinski_fajwel">Fajwel Kempiński</persName> 21</p>
					<p>17. <persName ref="#ehri_et_zygielbaum_mojzesz">Mojżesz Zygielbaum</persName> 21</p>
					<p>18. <persName ref="#ehri_et_zygielbaum_ajzyk">Ajzyk Zygielbaum</persName> 23</p>
					<p>19. <persName ref="#ehri_et_szmilewicz_szlama">Szlama Szmilewicz</persName> 34</p>
